28 July 2010The Minister of Women, Children and Persons with Disabilities, Noluthando Mayende-Sibiya will on Monday, 2 August 2010, launch the 2010 Women s Month programme. Minister Mayende-Sibiya will also introduce the theme for the month and report on progress made since 1994 with regards to women empowerment.Members of the media are invited as follows:Date: Monday, 2 August 2010 Time: 11h00 Venue: Room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaNB: There will be a video link to Imbizo Media Centre in Parliament, Cape Town.Members of the media wishing to attend are requested to forward their names to Professor Ndawonde on 078 845 7405/0784565738 or Tuso Zibula on 072 127 1565.For media enquiries contact: Sibani Mngadi Cell: 082 7720 161For media enquiries contact:Bongiwe Gambu Cell: 082 714 9463Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)